the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":75,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":84,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Joliffe was born in 1140, in Jacobstow, Cornwall, England, his father, Richard Joliffe, was 30 and his mother, Grace Colwil, was 26. He married Mary Baker on 3 April 1182, in Jacobstow, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died on 19 May 1240, in his hometown, at the age of 100."},"et":{"1140–19 May 1240":"1140–19. mai 1240","1140–1240":"1140–1240","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1164–1220":"1164–1220","1194–1273":"1194–1273","1110–1173":"1110–1173","1114–Female":"1114–Surnud","20 Mar 1194":"20. märts 1194","1110":"1110","1220":"1220","28 April 1173":"28. aprill 1173","19 May 1240":"19. mai 1240","1164":"1164","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1140":"1140","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","1238":"1238","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1114":"1114","27 January 1220":"27. jaanuar 1220","1135":"1135","3 april 1182":"3. aprill 1182","20 March 1164":"20. märts 1164","England":"England","Guiseley, Yorkshire, England":"Guiseley, Yorkshire, E